The project GLOCAL 2015 (Grant Opportunities for Learning in european Countries Aimed at promoting local development) fits the local, regional (Campania) context where has arisen which is particularly affected by the problem of youth unemployment. According to ISTAT (National Institute of Statistics), the main supplier of official statistical information in Italy, most recent national accounts data for the third quarter of 2014, the unemployment rate for the population aged 15 and older for both genders is of 20.29%. The situation does not improve when it comes to the region’s economic base largely composed of SMEs constantly encountering difficulties in recruiting adequately trained and specialised human resources. 
In this direction mobility action works, contributing to the growth of the local area in terms of employability, qualifying human resources, transfer of know-how acquired during the very professional work experience gained abroad through the Erasmus Plus programme.
The objectives are:
-guaranteeing valid and qualifi(yng)ed transnational working internships yielding positive effects on the curriculum of the beneficiaries and on an innovative and professional training-working system (economy/entrepreneurial);
-to improve the quality and development of the European cooperation in the field of vocational education and training (scholastic/post-scholastic education sector);
-to increase opportunities for professional mobility within the EU promoting the knowledge of a different workplace than the ones prevailing in the beneficiaries’ country of origin, improving tools and methodologies to meet demand and supply of qualifications;
-to promote an on-the-job training pattern created by assessing and addressing the training needs in the given local context;
-to improve the level of involvement of the entrepreneurial business and educational community, facilitating diffused connections, characterised by permanent and not occasional interactions, and investing on a young and “unprovincial” workforce;
-to consolidate the concept of active citizenship promoting a sense of belonging to a European “We”;
-to acquire know-how in the aerospace sector exploitable in the European context for the participation as support to the operations of ISS (International Space Station) and Exploration Program and in projects collaborating with companies and Research centers in Europe;
-to contribute enrichment/integration of "Repertorio di qualifiche professionali" in Campania Region, through the individuation of specific key competences in the aerospace sector by the valorisation of mobility experiences.

The participants will be 150 youngs and recent high school graduates (students who have graduated within the last 12 months) of a VET school and living in Campania. As beneficiaries of the project they will carry out work experiences in the following European countries: United Kingdom, Spain, Ireland, Belgium. The methodology for implementing the project meets the criteria of mutual support, mutual ongoing monitoring and evaluation of the project; it is a methodology that will involve all the partners and even the beneficiaries. The main tasks and responsibilities distributed among the applicant and the Consortium are:
-identification of the hosting companies and definition of the training agreement;
-selecting and booking of flight round trip tickets;
-finding and renting of accommodation for the participants;
-organising the airport transfer service to/from the participants’ homeplace/country of destination;
-insurance coverage for employment-related accidents and civil liability;
-pocket money as a monetary contribution to cover meals and local transfers;
-continuous monitoring and tutoring of project action.

The project results imply for beneficiaries (the ‘trainees’) the encounter with and “on field” experimentation of a labor market of European dimension, in order to further transfer the knowledge acquired during the work placement abroad once back to their country of origin. The participation in a 120 days (4 months) stay abroad will allow the beneficiaries (trainees) to acquire and develop an in-depth knowledge of the lifestyle of the host country increasing his/her curricular, cultural and professional baggage (the improvement and enrichment of language skills in general and, more specifically, the technical-specialised sub-vocabularies). An impact of relevant importance given by the project implementation is closely related to the partnership put in place with positive effects combining the strengthening of an already existing cooperation and the expansion of new opportunities for regional and European cooperation. Most of the results and impacts above mentioned will produce advantages and long-term benefits highlighted as follows: increased self-confidence, self-esteem and professional autonomy awareness of the trainees; availability of an appropriately skilled workforce for local/foreign potential employers.

The Amalfi Coast is an area geared to tourism recognized throughout the world. This should encourage the awareness of its potential among the young generations and of the need to train professionals so that they could make the history and fortunes of the hospitality industry in the area. Also, there is a need to open the way to some places along the winding road of tourism.



In an age in which students graduating from HEI are called to make a lifestyle choice, it is even more necessary to have an exchange of real information on the quality and effectiveness of their studies as well as on the real employment opportunities on the labour market, especially the local one. 

The proximity to the local tourism industry, the demand for skilled professionals in tourism enterprises and the opportunity for graduates to access the labour market, immediately after their graduation, highlight the importance and effectiveness of the attendance of VET Institutes focused on environment and tourism.



In this perspective, the Municipality of Vietri sul Mare promotes the sectorial mobility project "T.U.R.I.AR.T-Training Opportunities for young gRaduated In ARt and Tourism" for the implementation of 50 internships in EU in the field of tourism and environmental heritage promotion and development.



The project is addressed to 50 recent graduates entering the labour market who on the date of the notice publication satisfy the following requirements: age of majority; Italian citizenship; residence in the Campania Region; status of unemployment/inactivity and full civil and political rights; good command of the host Country language; VET school-leaving certificate in one of the following disciplines: administration and marketing, environment, agriculture, agribusiness and rural development, food and wine, hospitality, craft and industrial production, commercial business; 

With the same score, priority will be given to young people residing in one of the towns of the Amalfi Coast participating in the project. 



The project will last 24 months (from July 1st 2014 to June 30th 2016). The 120-days internships will be implemented between January 2015 and May 2016 in the following Countries: Spain, United Kingdom, and Malta.



During their stay abroad, beneficiaries will be supported by Vietri City Council, local partners and receiving organisations through the provision of the following services:



• definition of the training plan; 

• flight booking;

   airport meet and greet;

• accommodation in the city of destination; 

• insurance coverage for workplace accidents and civil liability; 

• supply of a pocket money to cover the subsidence expenses (food) and local transports.



By increasing the professional skills of human resources, the project aims to promote and develop tourism  industry in the Amalfi Coast and to disseminate practices and methodologies implementing a kind of sustainable development. It also seeks to promote and develop a kind of "European culture of tourism", creating positive synergies between local professionals’ prior knowledge and the different experiences and techniques of the European Countries involved.



In light of these considerations, the project T.U.R.I.AR.T represents one of the auspicious actions, as it refers both to the beneficiaries of the grant, who will improve their professional skills, and to the local area they belong, which will indirectly benefit from the raising awareness and project promotion processes, as well as from the know how of the participants, as workers in the sector, who will transfer the innovative practices and preservation processes learned during their work experience abroad.



These general purposes correspond to the following specific purposes referred to the participants: to foster professional growth and improvement of language and social skills, projecting recent graduates in the European Union context and focusing the mobility action on the improvement of their skills in the field of tourism and environment; to promote transnational exchanges among young professionals in the sector; to form a skilled labour force in the field of tourism marketing and promotion.

I.C.T. is a mobility project with a training period abroad , for  50  young people, students and new graduates belonging to or coming from Institute in Fuscaldo, of which:
- 20 VET students belonging to the 4th and 5th year addressed in the service sector for electronics, information technology, mechanics and energy. Is provided a theoretical and practical internship at Vocational Training Institutes located in Spain and the United Kingdom with for the above areas of study for 3 weeks;  they, being minors, will be accompanied, by 2 teachers of the school 
- 30 young VET students (graduated within 1 year from obtaining the qualification ) from the above-mentioned institutions and qualified in the fields referred to above. Is provided a practical internship in companies operating in Spain and the United Kingdom for a period of 17 weeks.
The general objectives of the project I.C.T. , are listedbelow:
- The recipients support the acquisition of skills in order to enhance their personal development and their employability in the European labor market ;
- Encourage the participants , the development of basic and transversal skills such as  learning digital skills and entrepreneurship ;
- Improving the knowledge of foreign languages;
- To increase the awareness and knowledge of the European and intercultural learning, in order to encourage a more active participation in society , developing a sense of identity and European citizenship;
- Promote consistency and comparability of different tools for the recognition of qualifications and competences between the different EU countries in order to facilitate a recognition of the same beyond their national borders;
- Develop local partnerships and transnational context , between the education system and the enetrprises
- Spread and disseminate the results of the project in order to give added value to the projects funded by the European Union .
The activities to be carried out will be:
- INFORMATION AWARENESS :
Actions: dissemination and publication of information material , newsletters , meetings, media website , seminars , final conference;
- SELECTION :
Actions: recruitment and selection of participants and of the beneficiaries ;
- PREPARATION OF MOBILITIES :
Actions: travel arrangements , housing , insurance, information on the safety and protection of participants, preparatory meetings with partners receiving virtual host , choosing the type of activities to be performed during the internship in agreement with the students and partners receivers welcome in foreign countries ; activities of back office administrative, organizational and management ;
- CULTURAL AND PEDAGOGICAL PREPARATION :
Actions: cultural and pedagogical preparation to facilitate the cultural and working approach to the country of destination and conclusion of the learning agreement
- MOBILITY:
Actions: Proceedings of the internship.
- MONITORING :
Actions: Report  trainees, analysis of the communications between the company tutor , partners, intermediaries , Final Report of the host ; Evaluation Form from company Tutor; assessment questionnaire administered to trainees at the end of internship , final reports by both trainees of business mentors ; questionnaire follow-up .
EVALUATION AND VALIDATION OF LEARNING OUTCOMES :
Validation of credits for students in the 4th and 5th year on the basis of the criteria set out in the MoU , and for graduates.
- DISSEMINATION:
Action for dissemination of results , direct to individual beneficiaries , the transnational partnership and local users .
The experience of mobility will have a positive impact on the following aspects :
- Improving the capacity and operational practices in the areas of reference ( electronics and electrotechnics, information technology and  telecommunications, mechanics and energy)
- Consolidation of technical and professional knowledge ;
- Working knowledge of other markets and other economies ;
- Improvement of the skills and knowledge of languages;
- Knowledge of specific software and the best digital and computer skills ;
- Familiarization with socio-cultural contexts of other EU countries , which increase the sense of European citizenship;
- Development of soft skills , communication , organizational and problem solving skills ;
- Greater comparability of the system of credit recognition, through the use of the methodology ECVET ;
- Exchange of good practice.
